<div align="center"><h2>Welcome to Everquest Online</h2></div><br />
<b>Everquest Online</b> is a fan site with plenty of information about the online MMORPG from Sony: <i>Everquest</i>.<br />
<br />
<i>Everquest</i> is the largest online roleplaying game to date with over 400,000 subscribers world-wide, 6 expansions, over 40 servers, and fan fairs with the most active and close-knit community around.<br />
<br />
The multitude of activities you can do in Everquest are:<ul><li>Choose from 15 different and unique races</li><li>Become one of 16 different classes, each with their own skills and abilities</li><li>Fight in large scale battles</li><li>Defeat enormous monsters</li><li>Buy and Sell to become a wealthy merchant</li><li>Join parties and groups to go hunting and questing with</li><li>Collect thousands of items</li><li>Learn thousands of spells to cast</li></ul>
<hr><br />
<h2>Announcement: Submit Your Everquest Guide!</h2>&nbsp;posted&nbsp;Sunday, July 25, 2004 9:57 AM EDT (  <a href="http://www.everquest-online.com/cgi-bin/admin/printnews.cgi?newsid1090767465,499," target="_blank"><img src="http://www.everquest-online.com/content/templates/1/images/print.gif" height="11" width="15" border="0" alt="Printer Friendly Page" /></a> <a href="http://www.everquest-online.com/cgi-bin/admin/sendnews.cgi?newsid1090767465,499," target="_blank"><img src="http://www.everquest-online.com/content/templates/1/images/mail.gif" height="11" width="15" border="0" alt="Send this Article to a Friend" /></a> )<br />You can now submit your <b>EQ Guide</b> to us on our <a href="http://www.everquest-online.com/content/everquest-addguide.php" class="newslink">Add Guide page</a>. Special rewards for unique and thorough guides. Please submit your personal work only, do not copy someone else's guide.<br /><br /><div align="center"><h1>EQ Everquest News</h1></div>
<br />
<h2>EQlizer News</h2>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<i>Tuesday October 19, 2004</i><br />alt 2004-10-19 Submit to EQ'Lizer, Get In EQ 2 Beta Posted by : J.C. Smith I am proud to announce a new contest here at EQ'Lizer, that gives our readers a shot at earning a spot in the Everquest 2 beta test. We've been granted the ability to give away thirty Everquest 2 beta slots over the course next three weeks. I've been playing the game myself now for a while, and I've been having a blast. Now you have your chance. Here's how it works. Matt will be setting up a contest page some time this e...&nbsp;<a href="http://eqlizer.net/index.shtml" target="_blank">[read more]</a><br /><br /><h2>Allakhazams News</h2>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<i>Monday October 18, 2004</i><br />October 17, 2004 Here's another batch of updates for you. New Items: Shimmering ScaleBracer Chain Pyrique'sBelt Voidflow of Minor Aggression Stormflow of Minor Quickening Sodalite of Minor Sundering Skyflow of Minor Efficiency Emberflow of Minor Celerity Boneflow of Minor Sundering Bloodflow of Minor Sundering Waterflow of Minor Ferocity Woven Feran Hide Cloak Spell: Dirge of Metala BrutishGloves of Bashing Noc Claw Zulaqua's Cloak Updated Items: Silken Turbanof Serfdom Shimmering ScaleBracer C...&nbsp;<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/" target="_blank">[read more]</a><br /><br /><h2>EQ Vault News</h2>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<i>Monday October 18, 2004</i><br />Couple news items for Monday Print News Mail News Rather then posting multiple news items, easier to condense these into the same. Loral over at Mobhunter has a new update up today. The article focuses on the weaknesses of Omens of War. Here's a clip: The Omens task system could be the future of quests in Everquest. All of the tools are there to help players accomplish quests and travel across Norrath. While the current quest options are limited, scripted encounters and continuing story lines c...&nbsp;<a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/" target="_blank">[read more]</a><br /><br /><h2>Mobhunter News</h2>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<i>Monday October 18, 2004</i><br />The Warts Under the Emperor's Clothes by Loral on 18 October 2004 : t is a month after the release of Omens of War and the world of Norrath changed forever. While this expansion has many strengths, it also has a few weaknesses. This week we peek underneath the beautiful and ornate exterior to examine a few of the expansion s weaknesses. - 0 Comments Every time Loral writes an article, I have to order cases of extra flame....&nbsp;<a href="http://mobhunter.com/" target="_blank">[read more]</a><br /><br /><h2>Planet EQ News</h2>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<i>Saturday October 16, 2004</i><br />The EQ2 Beta NDA Has Been Lifted 10/15/04, 22:03 PST Muskie The Beta NDA has been Lifted Anyone who has been playing EQ2 in beta up to this point is now allowed to share their experiences in the game freely Go Hound your friends who got into the beta that you are so envious of And Beta-testers, post your experiences in the forums Oh Yeah. Hi all I'm back Sorry for the long absence :P Thursday, October 14, 2004...&nbsp;<a href="http://www.planeteq.com/" target="_blank">[read more]</a><br /><br /><h2>Township Rebellion News</h2>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<i>Friday October 15, 2004</i><br />Three Down, Three to Go Posted by adetia on October 15, 2004 at 08:27 EST 0 Comments Tacvi Bosses Fall One By One Posted by Jave on September 23, 2004 at 00:29 EST 0 Comments Pixtt Xxeric Kex Dead Posted by Jave on August 25, 2004 at 20:43 EST Tacvi First Boss 9 Comments TR's like a Timex, we take a lickin but keep on ticking Posted by Jave on August 24, 2004 at 20:13 EST TR's Fat Got Trimmed and our Lean Mean Killing Machine owned Zun in a perfect execution 0 Comments IMG SRC/images/spacer.gif...&nbsp;<a href="http://www.townrebels.org/" target="_blank">[read more]</a><br /><br /><h2>EQ Stratics News</h2>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<i>Thursday October 14, 2004</i><br />Thursday October 14 2004 Tonight's House of Commons Log Site News - 7:35 PM PDT We had a great Dev Chat tonight If you weren't able to make it you can still get all the info from it Right Here in the log Enjoy And stay tuned for a continued series of HoC chats, let us know what you'd like to see in them Comment on this article - LordOfDreams EQ2 Beta Giveaway Stratics Network Announcement - 5:15 PM PDT Stratics brings to you their EverQuest2 Beta Giveaway. Each week for three weeks running, we...&nbsp;<a href="http://eq.stratics.com/" target="_blank">[read more]</a><br /><br /><h2>Safehouse News News</h2>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<i>Thursday October 14, 2004</i><br />1 , 2 Next - The Safehouse is giving away 10 EverQuest II beta accounts 10-14-2004 09:37:36 am by Aidden Post your Comments 0 The Safehouse and its staff are happy to announce our latest Safehouse raffle. 10 EverQuest II beta accounts will be given away to lucky winners randomly picked. The raffle starts today and you can sign up by heading over to the Safehouse Raffle page The Rules for this raffle are as follows: Each Registered Safehouse member may enter once. The Shraffle tool is designed t...&nbsp;<a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org/" target="_blank">[read more]</a><br /><br /><br /><br /><b><a href="http://wetrack.it/yantis/af.cgi?aid=919&redirect=http://www.mysupersales.com/">MySuperSales</a> is the best place for the cheapest Platinum and top items at the lowest prices</b>
